               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Qirqos "Vita of Cyricus" (fols. 3ra-7vb, 36va-vb, 36ra-rb,
                     8ra-20vb, 35va-vb, 35ra-rb, 21ra-34vb), incomplete&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-2;
                     colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="fols. 3ra"
                        to="7vb, 36va-vb, 36ra-rb, 8ra-20vb, 35va-vb, 35ra-rb, 21ra-34vb">fols.
                        3ra-7vb, 36va-vb, 36ra-rb, 8ra-20vb, 35va-vb, 35ra-rb, 21ra-34vb</locus>
                     <title type="incomplete">Gadla Qirqos “Vita of Cyricus"</title>

                     <incipit>
                        <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>: በስመ፡”…ገድል፡ ወስምዕ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ወብፁዕ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ወዘእሙ፡
                        ኢየሉጣ፡ ወዘካልአንሂ፡ ፼፡ ወ[er.]፲፻፡ ወ፭፡ ፻፡ ወ፴፡ ወ፬ሰማዕት፡ እለ፡ ተከለሉ፡ በመዋዕለ፡
                        እስህንድሮስ፡[sic] [<locus target="#3v">3v</locus>] ንጉሠ፡ ግብጽ፡ ...<foreign
                           xml:lang="en">
                           <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>: In the name of the Father and of the
                           Son and of the Holy Spirit, one God, (this is) the combat and the
                           martyrdom of saint and blessed Cyricus, and of his mother Julitta and of
                           other 11,534 martyrs who were crowned in the time of Alexander, king of
                           Egypt …</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <locus target="#34va">34va</locus>, l.3: …ወተከለሉ፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፭ለሠርቀ፡ ጥር፡ ወሀሎ፡ ቅዱስ፡
                        ቂርቆስ፡ ወትረ፡ ይቀውም፡ በየማነ፡ መንበሩ፡ ለእግዚኣብ̱ሔር፡ ወተንብል፡ በእንቲአነ፡ ኀበ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ዘለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡
                        አሜን፡ ወአሜን፨ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፨--፨<foreign xml:lang="en">
                           <locus target="#34va">34va</locus>, l.3: …and they were crowned on 15<hi
                              rend="apices">th</hi> of the month of Ṭǝrr. And St Cyricus always
                           stands on the right side of the throne of God and [he is] an intercessor
                           for us in front of the eternal King. Amen and Amen. Let it be, let it
                           be.</foreign>
                     </explicit>
