                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1"> f. 34va, l.14: ተፈጸመ፡ በዝየ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ገድሉ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ቂርቆስ፡
                        ወዘእሙ፡ [<locus target="#34vb">34vb</locus>] ኢየሉጣ፡  ዘፈጸሙ፡ ገድሎሙ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ እለ፡
                     እስክንድሮስ፡ ንጉሥ፡ በእንተ፡ ስሙ፡ ለክርስቶስ፨ ጸሎቶሙ፡ ወበረከቶሙ፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ደቂቆሙ፡ ተዓሬየነ፡ እግዚእ፡ ምስለ፡
                     ዘመልአክ፡ ወምስለ፡ ኵልነ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ዛቲ፡ መካን፡ ወምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሃ። [ኃ]ጥዕ፡ ወአባሲ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡
                        አሜ[ን።]<locus target="#34va">34va</locus>, l.14: Herewith the Life of Saint
                     Cyricus and of his mother Julitta was completed, who finished their lives
                     during the time of King Alexander for the sake of the name of Christ. Their
                     prayer and their blessing be with their children Täʿareyännä ʾƎgziʾ with
                     Za-Mälʾak and with all of us, children of this place, and with her (the book’s)
                     scribe, sinner and impious <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam"
                        >Zawalda Māryām</persName>. For ever and ever, amen. </colophon>
